{"type":"message","id":"1bf1032c","parentId":"958fb4bf","timestamp":"2026-04-15T00:33:11.890Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me analyze the active sessions. From the sessions_list output, I need to find all sessions with `status: \"running\"`.\n\nLooking at the sessions:\n\n1. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:e7885813-0446-4101-a171-941c2416848e` — status: \"running\" — this is the current cron session (Agent Status to Lead) — startedAt: 1776213151282 (current time 00:32 UTC) — ~3m\n2. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:ed2d0b5d-fc56-42eb-a8fc-973a48024df7` — status: \"running\" — 5p QLHV progress monitor — startedAt: 1776207735553 (00:22 UTC) — ~1h 10m\n\n\n3. `agent:master-orchestrator:cron:6f3323ef-607e-42a0-b946-611913081d31` — status: \"running\" — DTLX 5p progress monitor — startedAt: 1776199558073 (~23:59 UTC) — ~1h 33m\n4. `agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134` — status: \"running\" — the telegram direct session with Lead is also active.\n5. `agent:master-orchestrator:subagent:c2d275a5-d70a-4775-a268-fecf4708f133` — this one's marked as done, so I'll skip it. Looking at the running sessions, I need to filter out the cron job that started this check at 00:32 UTC, which leaves me with the three other cron jobs and the Telegram direct session still active.\n\nThe 5p QLHV progress monitor's been running about an hour and ten minutes since 00:22 UTC, the DTLX 5p progress monitor for roughly an hour and thirty-three minutes since just before midnight, and the Telegram direct session started at 00:22 UTC. The Telegram direct session ended at 00:24 UTC after about 9 seconds, but the status still shows as \"running\" with an endedAt timestamp, which is contradictory. The last message was from this cron session around 00:22 UTC, so the session appears to be in a completed state despite the running status indicator. was this agent status report sent by cron:e7885813 to lead via telegram. The telegram:direct session has `status: running` but `endedAt` is set to `1776212660602` which is 00:24 UTC. And the last message from lead was the agent status report at 00:22 UTC.\n\nLooking at the stopped reason: \"stop\" at 00:24 UTC. So the session ended but the status is still \"running\". This might be a stale status display. But for our purposes, the telegram:direct session was active until ~00:24 UTC, which is recent.\n\nBut actually, it could be that the telegram:direct session is still technically \"running\" (awaiting new messages) but just had endedAt set. Or it might be a stale entry.\n\nLet me focus on what matters. I have 4 active sessions total including the current cron. Excluding this cron, I have 3 active sessions: the QLHV 5p monitor running for about an hour and ten minutes since 00:22 UTC, the DTLX 5p monitor running for roughly an hour and thirty-three minutes since 23:59 UTC, and the Telegram direct session with Lead that started at 00:22 UTC and has been active for about nine seconds.\n\nThe telegram:direct session has an endedAt timestamp that suggests it might have stopped, but given the status shows running and the last message was just sent at 00:22 UTC, I'll include it in the count. Now I need to calculate the exact durations for each session and prepare the status report. The QLHV session has been running for about 1h10m since 00:22 UTC, while the DTLX session started at 23:59 UTC and is approaching 1h33m. Looking back at the last report from 00:22 UTC, I can see what was active at that time—the QLHV 5p monitor and DTLX 5p monitor were both running, plus a Telegram direct session with Lead that started around 00:22 UTC. Now at 00:32 UTC, that Telegram session appears to still be active, though it ended briefly just a few minutes later. The Telegram direct session has ended and been replaced by a new one, while the other three sessions are still running. The DTLX 5p monitor spawned some child sessions that have already completed, but those aren't relevant to what I need to track right now.","thinkingSignature":"620bda1f32f7ea2302960e21b42592bd4759ce95b78b987c0bd19837b0866373"},{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile the report and send it to Lead.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_if6ez1tf7k95_1","name":"sessions_send","arguments":{"sessionKey":"agent:master-orchestrator:telegram:direct:6053576134","message":"🌐 Orbis — Agent Status | 00:32 UTC 15 Apr\n\nActive sessions: 3\n• cron:ed2d0b5d (QLHV 5p): running — 5p progress monitor — ~1h 10m\n• cron:6f3323ef (DTLX 5p): running — 5p progress monitor DTLX — ~1h 33m\n• telegram:direct: running — Lead direct session — ~10m\n\nPipeline: HEALTHY ✅\n• MCP: stitch ✅ confluence ✅ gitlab ✅\n• Blockers: none\n\n— Orbis 🌐","timeoutSeconds":30}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":24664,"output":1223,"cacheRead":13849,"cacheWrite":309,"totalTokens":40045,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776213161512,"responseId":"062e0faae31a4a861f4ebde0e0867395"}}
